#!CDarkGreen #!N  #!Rchvudir Changing Your Viewing Direction 
#!N #!EC #!N #!N Data Explorer allows you to choose from 
several defined viewing directions. To change the view: #!N #!I0 #!N 
 #!F-adobe-times-medium-r-normal--18*   #!N #!N #!I30 #!N 1. Select the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Set View 
#!EF option box in the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   View Control... #!EF dialog box. 
While the mouse button is pressed down, an option box listing 
different view options appears. These choices are illustrated in  #!Lsvdb56,dxall301 f Figure 56  #!EL  . 
#!Cbrown #!N  #!F-adobe-times-medium-r-normal--18*    #!Rsvdb56 #!N #!T,1,66 #!N TAB None #!N TAB 
Top #!N TAB Bottom #!N TAB Front #!N TAB Back #!N 
TAB Left #!N TAB Right #!N TAB Diagonal #!N TAB Off 
Top #!N TAB Off Bottom #!N TAB Off Front #!N TAB 
Off Back #!N TAB Off Left #!N TAB Off Right #!N 
TAB Off Diagon|l Figure 56. Set View Option Box #!EF #!N 
#!EC Choose to view the object from the top, bottom, front, 
back, left, right, or diagonal view. Because a head-on view of 
an object tends to detract from the 3-D quality,  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Off 
#!EF options are provided to skew the image slightly. To select 
an option, move the mouse so that the desired option is 
highlighted, then release the mouse button. The image is redisplayed with 
the new view. #!N #!I0 #!N #!EF #!N #!N #!N #!N 
